Print species-area relationship summary

Source: R/print.SAR.R
print.SAR.Rd

Function for printing the summary of species-area relationship objects from the SSARP::SARP() function

Usage

# S3 method for class 'SAR'
print(x, printlen = NULL, ...)

Arguments

x

The SAR object of interest

printlen

Should always be NULL

...

Parameters to pass to print()

Value

The summary of your species-area relationship

Examples

if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{
seg <- SARP(occurrences)
print(seg)
} # }
